			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				gnomes are by far my favorite race.  I have 2 characters who are gnomes, and both are very enjoyable to play.  I have a gnomish warrior who is awsome, he can solo white cons without taking any dmg, and that is because he has very high agility.  Sure an ogre can bash for many dmg, but he also takes many dmg, gnomes hit fast and dodge many hits.  Besides being good fighters, they also make awsome casters. I have a gnomish magician, and I love him, if played correctly, a pure caster can be mighty powerful, ye just need to know how to play them.  For example, with my magician i have noticed that the best way to win agains a yellow con is to cast on the baddie, then tank it with me dagger.  I will take about 5 hits until I am at 2 bubs of health, then i back off and me pet  takes the rest of the dmg while i blast the baddie.  I found that if the baddie is attacking me while botjh my pet and I bash it, my pet never dies.  the other option is to let your pet tank the whole time while you blast the baddie.  This is an ok strategy on even cons or blues, but on yellows, your pet will get to low health or die while you are casting.  so, if you are considering becoming a gnome, i bid ye god luck, and you shall have much fun, as they are a great race, best in norrath!  (except for dwarves! dwarves are the best cleric race!) look out for dibi, or smib on the bertoxxulous server.<BR>
